<div class='commentbox'>
I made my second trip down Big Creek last weekend. While Mill Rapid was fun at 2.5 feet, I wanted<br/>
to confirm what has already been mentioned in the comments. There is no legal method of entering<br/>
the river where it nears Forrest Road. The landowner allowed us to put-in that day, but he stated<br/>
clearly that we were not to do so again. And it doesn't matter if shuttle is arranged or if you<br/>
park elsewhere, he does not want people crossing his property to get to the river. </div>
</td>
</tr>
